---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 13
  Paragraph: 40
Title: The Way Of Heaven
---
Duke Huan was in his hall reading a book. The wheelwright P'ien, who
was in the yard below chiseling a wheel, laid down his mallet and
chisel, stepped up into the hall, and said to Duke Huan, "This book
Your Grace is reading - may I venture to ask whose words are in it?"
